{
  "texts": [
    "Empty grid boxes are filtered before using grid data to train a machine-learning modelThe molecular docking and cavity detection methods exhibit missing values with a failure ratio ranging from 0 to 2% on the training set.",
    "Among the considered software applications, namely GalaxyDock, PLANTS, Vina, and Fpocket, it is seen that the former three exhibit a failure ratio of 2%, however, Fpocket demonstrates a comparatively lower failure ratio of 1%.",
    "Fortunately, both ZDOCK and P2rank do not exhibit any missing data.",
    "The failures observed in the blind docking of CoBDock can be attributed to the utilization of huge search sizes.",
    "The huge search size requires high memory usage."
  ]
}